# 5. ウェディングショーの舞台裏

Nene: So, we ended up training a lot together and we both performed at the Fan Festival.
Ena: Wow, I didn't realize you two worked so hard.
Honami: I knew that Hanasato was an incredible person, but so are you, Kusanagi.
Nene: N-No, I'm really nothing special...
Minori's Voice: Everyone! I'm all ready!
Nene: Oh...! That sounded like...
Ena: Minori, right? Thank goodness. That means our thirty minutes are up.
Comments: <Thanks, Nene and Minori's other friends!> <We got to hear some good stories.>
Honami: Hehe. Nice work, Kusanagi.
Nene: Thank you all very much. I couldn't have done this without you.
Ena: You're welcome. But to be fair, all we really did was chat.
Ena: Anyway, I guess it's time for Minori to dazzle us all.
Shiho: Right. Are you ready, Minori?
Minori's Voice: Ready!
Minori's Voice: Thank you all very much for your patience!
Minori's Voice: The newlywed bride, Minori Hanasato, will now enter! I hope you'll all give her a big round of applause!
Minori: Ta-daa!
Minori: Hehe. Look how I've transformed...!
Minori: H-How do I look? Oh, lemme spin around for you♪ Haha.
Comments: <That looks amazing on you!> <Pink suits you really well.> <You look so adorable. My eyes are starting to well up.>
Minori: Hehe... Thanks, everyone!
Nene: That does look really amazing on you, Hanasato...!
Honami: I agree! Oh, look at all the flowers on this dress. That's so cute.
Ena: And this color's perfect. It really suits your sunny personality, Minori.
Shiho: Yeah, you do look amazing in it.
Minori: Hehe. I'm probably blushing like crazy from all this praise...
Comments: <No fair! I wanna try on a dress too!> <I might try going there if I can.>
Nene: Your viewers seem interested in actually coming here. All because of your hard work, Hanasato.
Honami: I'm so glad for you!
Minori: No, I've done hardly anything! More importantly, I need to thank all of you for doing that segment while I was gone!
Comments: <That was fun!> <I learned today that Minori is Minori wherever she goes.> <You should do another segment like this again sometime.>
Shiho: You're welcome. I'm just glad we were able to help.
Minori: Alright, now that I've changed into my dress, let's check out the next booth...
Minori: No, on second thought...! I'm sure you all have plans after this. Especially you, Nene. Don't you have to start getting ready for your show soon?
Ena: I'm actually free today, but what's this show you're talking about?
Minori: Oh, Nene's playing the lead in the show that's taking place later this evening!
Shiho: Oh, that could be fun... It might be worth seeing before heading home.
Honami: I agree! It'll be something we can tell the others about later.
Nene: Hehe. Thanks.
Nene: I'm actually still free for about the next hour, but I will have to go once that time comes...
Nene: Sorry, I need to take this call. It's Ms. Nozaki.
Minori: Okay!
Nene: Hello? This is Kusanagi. Yes... Okay...?
Nene: What? Yes, of course. I'll try asking her now...
Nene: Can we talk for a second, Hanasato? Ms. Nozaki has a proposal for you.
Minori: Huh? A proposal?
Nene: Yeah, she was wondering if you'd like to stream us getting ready for our show.
Minori: What?! B-But that's only for the staff to see, isn't it?! Is she sure about this?!
Nene: Yes. She said that she'd really appreciate it if you could include a sort of making-of segment...
Nene: I'd also like for everyone to see what goes on behind the scenes. The director and other cast members all worked really hard to make this show happen, after all.
Minori: Okay...! In that case, I'd love to!
Nene: Alright, I'll let Ms. Nozaki know.
Minori: Oh, but... If I'm headed backstage, then doesn't that mean we have to sort of part ways for now...?
Shiho: Right. They don't need a bunch of outsiders getting in the way back there.
Minori: *Sob* I'm so sorry... After asking you all to help me, too!
Ena: No, that's okay. We understand the position you're in.
Honami: Right. So, Hanasato, let's meet again in the audience when the show starts.
Minori: Okay!
Comments: <Thanks, everyone!> <They seem like really nice girls.> <Bye bye!>
Minori: Alright, this is the rehearsal room for the show! Can you guys see everything okay?
Comments: <Whoa, look at all the cast members!> <I've never seen anything like this before!> <Do you spend a lot of time in these kinds of places, Nene?>
Comments: <I'm seeing a lot of dresses and tuxedos. Are they all costumes?>
Minori: Oh, right! This show's about a wedding, so I guess it's natural for dresses and tuxedos to... Huh?
Minori: Why do these ones have wings on them...?
Nene: Oh, those costumes are for everyone playing the angels.
Minori: The angels?
Nene: Yeah, the wedding angels.
Nene: Actually, that probably isn't very helpful... So, mind if I gave you a brief overview of the story?
Minori: Yes, please! Take it away.
Nene: Today's performance is titled “The Happy Wedding Show,” and its theme revolves around putting together the happiest wedding possible in the style that you want.
Nene: My character, the protagonist, isn't sure at first if she even wants to hold a wedding at all.
Nene: That's when the wedding angels, the patrons of marriages, appear before her.
Nene: She gradually begins to change her mind as they show her various examples of different ceremonies.
Minori: Wow...! Wait, examples of different ceremonies... Does that include the train wedding and the one at the aquarium we talked about earlier today?
Nene: Yeah, that's right.
Nene: At the end, she's reminded of something very important when she sees a wedding take place at a live house.
Minori: Something very important...?
Nene: She's reminded of how she met her fiancé.
Nene: She met him when she went to see a concert for this one idol. After remembering what happened, she decides to have her wedding at a live house.
Minori: She decides to have her wedding at a live house because of that idol's concert...?! That's so beautiful!!!
Comments: <Marrying someone you met at a concert! Talk about living the dream!> <The wedding itself would probably feel like a concert too after inviting all your friends!>
Minori: Yeah, I know what you guys mean!
Nene: Anyway, that's about how the story goes for this show...
Minori: Thanks, Nene! I feel even more excited about seeing it now♪
Nene: Hehe. I'm glad to hear that.
Man: I'm also glad to hear you say that.
Minori: Huh?! Oh, and this is...?!
Nene: Oh, this is Mr. Okamura. He's the director of our show.
Okamura: It's a pleasure to meet you. And thank you for advertising our show like this.
Minori: No, thank you for coming over to talk to us! My name is Minori Hanasato!
Minori: Again, I'm very much looking forward to seeing the show!
Okamura: I really appreciate it. This show was built around the idea of showing everyone just how much fun weddings are. I hope that message comes across clearly.
Minori: How much fun weddings are...
Okamura: Have you noticed how fewer and fewer young people are holding weddings these days?
Okamura: Of course, they're all free to choose whether or not to actually have one. It's perfectly fine to decide against.
Okamura: But I fear that some of them will look back in regret by the time they've turned my age. That they missed an opportunity to share their happiness with others...
Okamura: Of course, the financial aspect can become a source of stress for many, but deciding against it without understanding what they have to offer seems like a bit of a shame.
Okamura: Which is why I want us to show just how much fun weddings are. So, Ms. Kusanagi, let's do our best today.
Nene: Yes, let's!
Minori: ...
Minori: (Mr. Okamura, Ms. Nozaki and Nene all feel the same way.)
Minori: (They want everyone watching to see that weddings are fun. Even just a little bit.)
Minori: Hehe... Now I'm more excited about seeing it!
Okamura: That's wonderful to hear. Now, the rest of us need to make our final preparations...
Staff Member: W-We have an emergency, Mr. Okamura...!
Okamura: Hm? Slow down. What's wrong?
Staff Member: It's one of the cast members. She tripped, and...
Minori & Nene: What...?!
